<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1654,1930]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,313,1654,1678]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[323,443,1654,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rameshi">
<emphasis box="[323,443,1654,1678]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">P. rameshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[503,673,1654,1678]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmindicus">
<emphasis box="[503,673,1654,1678]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">P. burmindicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
form a closely related species group with divided connective and aedeagus not having dorsal and ventral processes on the shaft. 
<taxonomicName box="[851,1006,1690,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jiuhuaensis">
<emphasis box="[851,1006,1690,1714]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">P. jiuhuaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may also belong to this group judging from the shape of the aedeagus. 
<taxonomicName box="[530,651,1726,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rameshi">
<emphasis box="[530,651,1726,1750]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">P. rameshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[808,978,1726,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="burmindicus">
<emphasis box="[808,978,1726,1750]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">P. burmindicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having gradually narrowed aedeagal shafts and in the presence of a large membranous mesal lobe on the male pygofer. Both species differ from 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">P. d i v a ricatus</emphasis>
in having aedeagal shafts long and sinuate, the gonopore subapical rather than apical and in lacking the basal and ventral processes on the aedeagal shaft.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="52" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,1654,1930]" pageId="11" pageNumber="52">
